  "name": "TestRunIsolatesMemoryStackBetweenTests",
  "description": "Discovers two isolation fixture goals, runs them sequentially in a single test.run, then checks that all results have Status == \u0027Pass\u0027.",
  "comment": null,
  "steps": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "text": "test.discover tests in \u0027_isolation\u0027, pattern=\u0027*.fixture.goal\u0027, recursive, write to %tests%",
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "Fresh-App-per-test guard. Runs two paired fixtures under test.run\nparallel=1: AIsolationPollute writes %shared_probe%=1; BIsolationProbe\nasserts %shared_probe% is null at entry. If the runner regressed to\nsharing MemoryStack, Probe would read the polluted value and fail.\nParallel=1 forces sequential execution so the ordering is deterministic.",
